The U.S. is unique among modern constitutional democracies in allowing justices to serve for decades without term or age limits. The Supreme Court TERM Act proposes 18-year term limits for justices, which would create a regular appointment process and ensure each president the opportunity to nominate two justices per four-year term. This could make the Court more representative of the nation and restore a constitutional balance to the three branches of the federal government. A majority of Americans are in favor of term limits.
